NAME: STEP Certificate in Anti Money Laundering (PANAMA)
EMAIL_FOOTER__C:
All course materials are provided via our online learning platform. In order to gain access to this you will need to navigate to www.cltint.com and log in using your unique username and password.

You should ensure that you log-on to the platform as soon as possible to access the resources available. Please check the course forum regularly as it will be used to share important course information. We would very much welcome your contribution to this so that all delegates can benefit from an interactive learning experience.

Please note that if you are self-funding your access to the platform will not be activated until payment has been received.

Your STEP Membership
It is mandatory to become a member of STEP and maintain your STEP membership while studying a STEP qualification. If you are new to membership, STEP will conatct you within 6-8 weeks of your enrolment to welcome you to the association, provide you with your login details for the STEP website, direct you to information about the Society's Code of Professional Conduct, and tell you how to pay your membership fees. Membership of STEP offers professionals a number of benefits including opportunities to network, learn and share insights and knowldge across borders and practice areas. Members also have the opportunity to get involved in STEP's activities locally, nationally and internationally, from developing their local branch to contributing to technical or public policy debate on a global level. Being a member will keep you up to date, enhance your profile and develop your skills in specific or more extensive areas. To find out more, contact STEP at +44(0)20 3752 3700 or step@step.org.

Should you have any queries please do not hesitate to contact the CLTI Team on +44(0)121 362 7733 or cltinternational@centlaw.com.

NAME: Best Interest Assessor (BIA) (IH)
EMAIL_FOOTER__C:
Please note that a light lunch will be provided on each day, could you please let us know of any dietary requirements you may have.
 
This module is assessed in two parts. The first is a written submission, based on a scenario. The second assessment is a reflective piece of an observation of a Best Interest Assessment being completed. Please ensure you have a date for this observation arranged before the course starts.
 
Please take care to read and understand the attached Module and Assessment Guide to familiarise yourself with the process and requirements for qualification. 
 
Also attached is the Getting Started Guide, this will help you through the essential stages you need in order to complete your application for the BIA Module, set up your University IT account and help you to familiarise yourself with the essential University sites and who you should contact if you need help.
 
 
Invoice:
Your invoice will follow and if you have paid online then this will be noted on the invoice.
Full payment must be received prior to the first day of training.
 
National Union of Students (NUS)
Bond Solon is pleased to announce our partnership with National Union of Students (NUS).
 
As you are undertaking the Best Interest Assessor (BIA) Qualifying Module qualification, you are now eligible to purchase an ‘NUS Extra’ discount card.
This card offers you hundreds of discounts with market leading brands, including:
  • Amazon - 5% discount
  • Apple - Up to 15% discount
  • The Economist - 12 issues for just £1 each
  • Odeon cinema - 25% discount
  • Pizza Express - 40% discount
  • The Co-operative Food - 10% discount
  • Asos - 10% discount
  • Office - 10% discount
We are committed to put our clients at the heart of Bond Solon and everything that we do, and we wanted to make you aware of this exclusive benefit. You can now save money while learning.

If you would like more information about the ‘NUS Extra’ discount card and how you can purchase one, please visit www.bondsolon.com/NUS partnership

Kind Regards
EMAIL_HEADER__C:
I confirm that you are now booked to attend the Bond Solon UCPPD Best Interest Assessor (BIA) Qualifying Module, validated by Teesside University.
 
University Enrolment
You are required to enrol with the University before attending the module. Please click on the below link and complete the form as soon as possible:
 
https://e-vision.tees.ac.uk/si_prod/sits.urd/run/siw_ipp_lgn.login?process=siw_ipp_app&code1=PSWK4019NCEPD&code2=0098&code3=GUEST
  
Where you are asked ‘who is responsible for paying your fees’, please select ‘other’ and in the field next to this type Bond Solon.
 
For any technical issues please contact the University Admissions Team on Tel: 01642 384110 .
 
The Blackboard
After enrolment, you will receive information on the University’s interactive online system called the Blackboard. The Blackboard includes:
  • BIA Module and Assessment Guide*
  • MCA Codes of Practice*
  • DoLS Codes of Practice*
  • Law Society Guidance*
  • Reading List
  • TU’s Guidelines for Presentation and Referencing
  • TU’s Policy for Confidentiality and Consent
  • Discussion Forum
 
*You must ensure that you have access to these components during the face-to-face module delivery. This can either be physical, such as printed or purchased, or an electronic copy via a tablet. 
 
You will also be required to submit your assessments via Blackboard.

The module will be delivered on the following dates:

Su número de candidato aparece en la parte superior de este correo electrónico y deberá mencionarlo siempre que sea posible cuando se ponga en contacto con nosotros. También tendrá que facilitarlo cuando envíe sus evaluaciones ICA.
 
Si está en LinkedIn, por favor únase a la red de ICT y al Grupo de Estudio aquí https://www.linkedin.com/groups/4246170 y tómese un momento para seguirnos en Twitter y Facebook https://twitter.com/ictcompliance https://www.facebook.com/ictcompliance, para actualizaciones y consejos útiles.
 
Esperamos que disfrute el curso. Si necesita ponerse en contacto con nosotros o con su tutor en cualquier momento, por favor hágalo a través de la Plataforma de Preguntas y Respuestas de la Plataforma de Aprendizaje, por correo electrónico a ict@int-comp.com o llamando al teléfono +44 (0) 121 362 7534.

EMAIL_FOOTER__C:
Your course materials are provided via our learning platform. In order to gain access to this you will need to navigate to www.cltint.com and log in using your unique username and password.
You should ensure that you log-on to the platform as soon as possible to access the resources available. Please check the notice board regularly as it will be used to share important course information. We would very much welcome your contribution to this so that all delegates can benefit from an interactive learning experience.

Please note that if you are self-funding your access to the platform will not be activated until payment has been received.
Please make a note of your candidate number as you will need it for the examination. Please ensure that you take photographic identification with you to the examination. The invigilator will check this before the examination commences.

Your Data
We are committed to protecting the privacy and security of your personal information. You can find out how we collect, use, share and protect your personal data by visiting our Privacy Policy which can be found online.

Your STEP Membership
It is mandatory to become a member of STEP and maintain your STEP membership while studying a STEP qualification. If you are new to membership, STEP will contact you within 6-8 weeks of your enrolment to welcome you to the association, provide you with your login details for the STEP website, direct you to information about the Society's Code of Professional Conduct, and tell you how to pay your membership fees. Membership of STEP offers professionals a number of benefits including opportunities to network, learn and share insights and knowledge across borders and practice areas. Members also have the opportunity to get involved in STEP's activities locally, nationally and internationally, from developing their local branch to contributing to technical or public policy debate on a global level. Being a member will keep you up to date, enhance your profile and develop your skills in specific or more extensive areas. To find out more, please see the full list of benefits at http://www.step.org/benefits or contact STEP at +44(0)20 3752 3700 or step@step.org
​
Should you have any queries please do not hesitate to contact the CLTI team on +44 (0)121 362 7733 or at cltinternational@centlaw.com

Your course materials are provided via our online learning platform. In order to gain access to this you will need to navigate to www.cltint.com and log in using your unique username and password.
You should ensure that you log-on to the platform as soon as possible to access the resources available. Please check the notice board regularly as it will be used to share important course information. We would very much welcome your contribution to this so that all delegates can benefit from an interactive learning experience.

Please note that if you are self-funding your access to the platform will not be activated until payment has been received.
Please make a note of your candidate number as you will need it for the examination. Please ensure that you take photographic identification with you to the examination. The invigilator will check this before the examination commences.

Your Data
We are committed to protecting the privacy and security of your personal information. You can find out how we collect, use, share and protect your personal data by visiting our Privacy Policy which can be found online.

Your STEP Membership
It is mandatory to become a member of STEP and maintain your STEP membership while studying a STEP qualification. If you are new to membership, STEP will contact you within 6-8 weeks of your enrolment to welcome you to the association, provide you with your login details for the STEP website, direct you to information about the Society's Code of Professional Conduct, and tell you how to pay your membership fees. Membership of STEP offers professionals a number of benefits including opportunities to network, learn and share insights and knowledge across borders and practice areas. Members also have the opportunity to get involved in STEP's activities locally, nationally and internationally, from developing their local branch to contributing to technical or public policy debate on a global level. Being a member will keep you up to date, enhance your profile and develop your skills in specific or more extensive areas. To find out more, please see the full list of benefits at http://www.step.org/benefits or contact STEP at +44(0)20 3752 3700 or step@step.org
​
Should you have any queries please do not hesitate to contact the CLTI team on +44 (0)121 362 7733 or at cltinternational@centlaw.com

NAME: ICA Certificate in Financial Crime Risk - HSBC - In-House
EMAIL_FOOTER__C: To help ensure you gain maximum benefit from the course, you will be required to pass an on-line assessment before attending the workshop. The assessment consists of 25 multi choice questions. It is essential that you both read and understand all course material before taking the assessment . The questions are not designed to assess your general experience but to test your knowledge of the course materials and your ability to apply that learning in an examination environment.  During the workshop you will have an opportunity to examine and consider practical examples and situations relevant to your learning.   Please note that it is compulsory to pass the online assessment BEFORE you attend the workshop. Not everyone has passed the multi-choice assessment first time and therefore you are strongly advised to set aside at least 12-16 hours study before attempting the formal assessment. Your firm will be charged if you withdraw before the end of the course or if you fail to complete the course and attend the workshop on the planned date. We hope you enjoy the course and if you need to get in touch with us or your tutor at any point, please do so by emailing us at clientservices@int-comp.org or calling us on +44 (0)121 362 7518.
EMAIL_HEADER__C: This programme has been designed by the International Compliance Association (ICA) in conjunction with HSBC and leads to an ICA Certificate in Financial Crime Risk. This is an industry recognised qualification, awarded in conjunction with Alliance Manchester Business School.   The course uses an integrated learning methodology consisting of our online learning platform, study and support material, an online multiple-choice assessment and a one-day interactive workshop.  Your workshop date is below and we'll email you approximately two weeks before the workshop to confirm locations and timings.

We would very much welcome your contribution to this so that all delegates can benefit from an interactive learning experience.

Please note that if you are self-funding your access to the platform will not be activated until payment has been received.

Your STEP Membership
It is mandatory to become a member of STEP and maintain your STEP membership while studying a STEP qualification. If you are new to membership, STEP will conatct you within 6-8 weeks of your enrolment to welcome you to the association, provide you with your login details for the STEP website, direct you to information about the Society's Code of Professional Conduct, and tell you how to pay your membership fees. Membership of STEP offers professionals a number of benefits including opportunities to network, learn and share insights and knowldge across borders and practice areas. Members also have the opportunity to get involved in STEP's activities locally, nationally and internationally, from developing their local branch to contributing to technical or public policy debate on a global level. Being a member will keep you up to date, enhance your profile and develop your skills in specific or more extensive areas. To find out more, contact STEP at +44(0)20 3752 3700 or step@step.org.

Should you have any queries please do not hesitate to contact the CLTI Team on +44(0)121 362 7733 or cltinternational@centlaw.com.

EMAIL_FOOTER__C:
Your Data
We are committed to protecting the privacy and security of your personal information. You can find out how we collect, use, share and protect your personal data by visiting our Privacy Policy which can be found online.

Your STEP Membership
It is mandatory to become a member of STEP and maintain your STEP membership while studying a STEP qualification. If you are new to membership, STEP will contact you within 6-8 weeks of your enrolment to welcome you to membership, provide you with your login details for the STEP website, direct you to information about the STEP’s Code of Professional Conduct, and tell you how to pay your membership fees. Membership of STEP demonstrates a commitment to high professional standards and continued professional development and offers a number of benefits, including opportunities to network, learn and share insights and knowledge across borders and practice areas. You will also have the opportunity to enhance your profile through our Member Directory and develop your skills in specific or more extensive areas via our CPD resources. To find out more, contact STEP at +44(0)20 3752 3700 or step@step.org.
​
Should you have any queries please do not hesitate to contact the CLTI team on +44 (0)121 362 7733 or at cltinternational@centlaw.com

EMAIL_FOOTER__C:
Submission of Statement/Report  
For the ‘Part 1 - Advanced Statement Report Writing - Written Evidence and Part 2 - Giving Evidence - Witness Familiarisation’ course, you are required to submit a statement or report, written by either yourself or a colleague, to Bond Solon four weeks in advance of the training. Please ensure that this is not from an on-going case that you or your organisation may be involved in. If you are unable to provide a statement or a report, one will be provided for you on the day.

Assessment Marking and Edexcel Registration Fees
You have opted to undertake the assessments linked to the course(s) that you have booked. Please find below a breakdown of the additional fees for the:

Marking of Assessments 
£25.00 + VAT per 2 day course 

Registration Fees
For a Certificate the payment is currently £90.00 + VAT per person for the registration of the 8-day Advanced Professional Certificate in Investigative Practice which includes the Edexcel verification and award.  

For an Award the payment is currently £45.00 + VAT per person for the registration of each Award (2-day module only) which includes the Edexcel verification and award. 

For an Award the payment is currently £55.00 + VAT per person for the registration of the 3-day Professional Award in Complaints Handling and Investigation which includes the Edexcel verification and award.

Please note that all Registration fees are non-refundable.
    
Assessment Process
Please find attached 
•    Assessment Manual 
•    QA Registration Form

Please read both documents which will provide you with further details on the assessment process and what you will be required to do.
Please print a copy of the assessment manual, and take it with you to all training modules 

Please note the QFORM100 must be submitted to the following email address Info@bondsolon.com  // joannewaddoups@qa-associates.co.uk (Delete as appropriate) 

Invoicing
Your invoice for the course and marking of assessments will be sent in the next few days.
Please note that on receipt of your registration form, our Independent Assessment Centre, QA Associates will invoice you for Registration fees [Delete if not applicable]. 

All bookings are subject to our Terms and Conditions attached.  

If you have any queries in relation to this email and the supporting attachments, please contact me.  

We hope you enjoy the course.

NAME: STEP Certificate in Anti Money Laundering (VC)
EMAIL_FOOTER__C:
All course materials are provided via our online learning platform. In order to gain access to this you will need to navigate to www.cltint.com and log in using your unique username and password.

You should ensure that you log-on to the platform as soon as possible to access the resources available. Please check the course forum regularly as it will be used to share important course information. We would very much welcome your contribution to this so that all delegates can benefit from an interactive learning experience.

Please note that if you are self-funding your access to the platform will not be activated until payment has been received.

Your STEP Membership
It is mandatory to become a member of STEP and maintain your STEP membership while studying a STEP qualification. If you are new to membership, STEP will conatct you within 6-8 weeks of your enrolment to welcome you to the association, provide you with your login details for the STEP website, direct you to information about the Society's Code of Professional Conduct, and tell you how to pay your membership fees. Membership of STEP offers professionals a number of benefits including opportunities to network, learn and share insights and knowldge across borders and practice areas. Members also have the opportunity to get involved in STEP's activities locally, nationally and internationally, from developing their local branch to contributing to technical or public policy debate on a global level. Being a member will keep you up to date, enhance your profile and develop your skills in specific or more extensive areas. To find out more, contact STEP at +44(0)20 3752 3700 or step@step.org.

Should you have any queries please do not hesitate to contact the CLTI Team on +44(0)121 362 7733 or cltinternational@centlaw.com.

You are required to complete the ICA Specialist Certificate in Money Laundering Risk in New Technology SCB as part of Standard Chartered Bank’s Correspondent Banking Risk Certification you recently registered for.

The Money Laundering Risk Certification consists of internal knowledge/process modules and an external course, run by ICA. The entire certification including the ICA course must be completed within 90 days of registration.

ICA Course Overview:
•    The course consists of reading materials and webinars. A mandatory final assessment must be successfully passed in order to complete the course.
•    Staff have two attempts to pass the final assessment. If unsuccessful, the course is locked and an approval process is initiated which may lead to further delays and result in Overdue status.

Please be aware of the 90 days timeframe and complete the required learning in the time provided.

NAME: ICA International Diploma In Anti Money Laundering (HK)
EMAIL_FOOTER__C:
We recommend that you attend all workshops as they really help bring the learning to life as well as provide guidance on how to approach your assessments. You’ll also get to meet other people on your course and benefit from shared experiences.

Your candidate number is listed at the top of this email and where possible should be quoted in all contact with us. You will also need this when submitting your ICA assessments.

If you’re on LinkedIn, please join the ICT Network and Study group here https://www.linkedin.com/groups/4246170 and take the time to follow us on Twitter https://twitter.com/ictcompliance and Facebook https://www.facebook.com/ictcompliance for useful updates and tips.

We hope you enjoy the course and if you need to get in touch with us or your tutor at any point, please do so through the Q&A platform on the Learning Platform, by emailing us at studentadmin@int-comp.com or calling us on +65 6500 0010.

NAME: 1252-CUBS - Business Skills for Experts
1022-APAIP Unit 1
EMAIL_FOOTER__C:
Laptop
For the ‘Open Source Internet investigations course’ and ‘The Effective and Lawful Use of the Internet in Investigations’ each delegate attending this course is required to bring with them to the training a lap top (not a tablet) which enables the use of WIFI.  The lap top must be free from network administrator lockdown.
 
Submission of Statement/Report 
For the ‘Part 1 - Advanced Statement Report Writing - Written Evidence and Part 2 - Giving Evidence - Witness Familiarisation’ course, you are required to submit a statement or report, written by either yourself or a colleague, to Bond Solon four weeks in advance of the training. Please ensure that this is not from an on-going case that you or your organisation may be involved in. If you are unable to provide a statement or a report, one will be provided for you on the day.
 
Assessment Marking and Edexcel Registration Fees
You have opted to undertake the assessments linked to the course(s) that you have booked. Please find below a breakdown of the additional fees for the:
 
Marking of Assessments
 
£25.00 + VAT per 2 day course
 
Registration Fees
 
For a Certificate the payment is currently £90.00 + VAT per person for the registration of the 8-day Advanced Professional Certificate in Investigative Practice which includes the Edexcel verification and award. 
 
For an Award the payment is currently £45.00 + VAT per person for the registration of each Award (2-day module only) which includes the Edexcel verification and award.
 
For an Award the payment is currently £55.00 + VAT per person for the registration of the 3-day Professional Award in Complaints Handling and Investigation which includes the Edexcel verification and award.
 
Please note that all Registration fees are non-refundable.
               
Assessment Process
Please find attached
  • Assessment Manual
  • QA Registration Form
 
Please read both documents which will provide you with further details on the assessment process and what you will be required to do. Please print a copy of the assessment manual, and take it with you to all training modules
 
Please note the QFORM100 must be submitted to the following email address Info@bondsolon.com  // joannewaddoups@qa-associates.co.uk (Delete as appropriate)
 
Invoicing
Your invoice for the course and marking of assessments will be sent in the next few days.
Please note that on receipt of your registration form, our Independent Assessment Centre, QA Associates will invoice you for Registration fees [Delete if not applicable].
 
All bookings are subject to our Terms and Conditions attached. 
 
If you have any queries in relation to this email and the supporting attachments, please contact me. 
 
We hope you enjoy the course.

Results
 
Results for this examination will be sent to you by email 35 working days after the examination take place.
 
Please note you will not receive notification of your results by post.  An email confirming your results will be sufficient proof for the Law Society when applying for membership. 
 
May we wish you every success with your examination.

Kind regards

Professional Accreditations
Tel:  0121 362 7526
Email:  immigration@clt.co.uk

Your Data We are committed to protecting the privacy and security of your personal information. You can find out how we collect, use, share and protect your personal data by visiting our Privacy Policy which can be found online. To access this please visit www.cltint.com/privacy-policy/ and www.step.org/privacy-notice . Your STEP Membership STEP will be in touch with you separately confirming your new member status shortly and you will be asked to log on to the STEP website to confirm your commitment to STEP by agreeing to a member declaration. Please note that you must do this within 30 days of receiving your confirmation email or your membership will be suspended and you will be unable to complete your studies on the programme with us. Further details can be found here ? www.step.org/join-us/your-commitment . Membership of STEP offers professionals a number of benefits including opportunities to network, learn and share insights and knowledge across borders and practice areas. Members will also have the opportunity to enhance their profile and develop their skills in specific or more extensive areas. To find out more about the benefits of becoming a STEP member, please visit www.step.org/benefits .   Should you have any queries at any time, please do not hesitate to contact the CLTI team on +44 (0)121 362 7733 or email us at cltinternational@centlaw.com . EMAIL_FOOTER__C:
All course materials, including an introductory module, the pre-reading for each masterclass and assessment guidance, are provided via our online learning platform. The introductory module has been designed to be your initial reference point for key information about the course, helping you to get started with your studies and answer frequently asked questions and we strongly recommend that you work through this first. 

To access to the online learning platform, you will need to navigate to https://onlinelearning.cltint.com/ and log in using your username and password (above).

You will also have access to the course discussion forum where knowledge, expertise and experience can be shared with your peers on the programme, and we will share useful information and reminders about the programme. Please note that you have been automatically subscribed to the discussion forum for this course and you will receive notification (by email) when posts are made.

Your Data
We are committed to protecting the privacy and security of your personal information. You can find out how we collect, use, share and protect your personal data by visiting our Privacy Policy which can be found online.

Your STEP Membership
It is mandatory to become a member of STEP and maintain your STEP membership while studying a STEP qualification. If you are new to membership, STEP will contact you within 6-8 weeks of your enrolment to welcome you to the association, provide you with your login details for the STEP website, direct you to information about the Society's Code of Professional Conduct, and tell you how to pay your membership fees. Membership of STEP offers professionals a number of benefits including opportunities to network, learn and share insights and knowledge across borders and practice areas. Members also have the opportunity to get involved in STEP's activities locally, nationally and internationally, from developing their local branch to contributing to technical or public policy debate on a global level. Being a member will keep you up to date, enhance your profile and develop your skills in specific or more extensive areas. To find out more, please see the full list of benefits at https://www.step.org/members/step-membership-benefits or contact STEP at +44(0)20 3752 3700 or step@step.org

Should you have any queries please do not hesitate to contact CLTI team on +44 (0) 121 362 7733 or cltinternational@centlaw.com

NAME: Best Interest Assessor (BIA) Public Training
EMAIL_FOOTER__C:
Please note that a light lunch will be provided on each day, could you please let us know of any dietary requirements you may have.
 
This module is assessed in two parts. The first is a written submission, based on a scenario. The second assessment is a reflective piece of an observation of a Best Interest Assessment being completed. Please ensure you have a date for this observation arranged before the course starts.
 
Please take care to read and understand the attached Module and Assessment Guide to familiarise yourself with the process and requirements for qualification. 
 
Also attached is the Getting Started Guide, this will help you through the essential stages you need in order to complete your application for the BIA Module, set up your University IT account and help you to familiarise yourself with the essential University sites and who you should contact if you need help.
 
 
Invoice:
Your invoice will follow and if you have paid online then this will be noted on the invoice.
Full payment must be received prior to the first day of training.
 
National Union of Students (NUS)
Bond Solon is pleased to announce our partnership with National Union of Students (NUS).
 
As you are undertaking the Best Interest Assessor (BIA) Qualifying Module qualification, you are now eligible to purchase an ‘NUS Extra’ discount card.
This card offers you hundreds of discounts with market leading brands, including:
  • Amazon - 5% discount
  • Apple - Up to 15% discount
  • The Economist - 12 issues for just £1 each
  • Odeon cinema - 25% discount
  • Pizza Express - 40% discount
  • The Co-operative Food - 10% discount
  • Asos - 10% discount
  • Office - 10% discount
We are committed to put our clients at the heart of Bond Solon and everything that we do, and we wanted to make you aware of this exclusive benefit. You can now save money while learning.

If you would like more information about the ‘NUS Extra’ discount card and how you can purchase one, please visit www.bondsolon.com/NUS partnership

Kind Regards
EMAIL_HEADER__C:
I confirm that you are now booked to attend the Bond Solon UCPPD Best Interest Assessor (BIA) Qualifying Module, validated by Teesside University.
 
University Enrolment
You are required to enrol with the University before attending the module. Please click on the below link and complete the form as soon as possible:
 
https://e-vision.tees.ac.uk/si_prod/sits.urd/run/siw_ipp_lgn.login?process=siw_ipp_app&code1=PSWK4019NCEPD&code2=0098&code3=GUEST
  
Where you are asked ‘who is responsible for paying your fees’, please select ‘other’ and in the field next to this type Bond Solon.
 
For any technical issues please contact the University Admissions Team on Tel: 01642 384110 .
 
The Blackboard
After enrolment, you will receive information on the University’s interactive online system called the Blackboard. The Blackboard includes:
  • BIA Module and Assessment Guide*
  • MCA Codes of Practice*
  • DoLS Codes of Practice*
  • Law Society Guidance*
  • Reading List
  • TU’s Guidelines for Presentation and Referencing
  • TU’s Policy for Confidentiality and Consent
  • Discussion Forum
 
*You must ensure that you have access to these components during the face-to-face module delivery. This can either be physical, such as printed or purchased, or an electronic copy via a tablet. 
 
You will also be required to submit your assessments via Blackboard.

The module will be delivered on the following dates:

Please check the course forum regularly as it will be used to share important course information. We would very much welcome your contribution to this so that all delegates can benefit from an interactive learning experience. Please note that if you are self-funding your access to the platform will not be activated until payment has been received . Please make a note of your candidate ID number as you will need it for the examination. Please ensure that you take photographic identification with you to the examination. The invigilator will check this before the examination commences. Your STEP Membership It is mandatory to become a member of STEP and maintain your STEP membership while studying a STEP qualification. If you are new to membership, STEP will conatct you within 6-8 weeks of your enrolment to welcome you to the association, provide you with your login details for the STEP website, direct you to information about the Society's Code of Professional Conduct, and tell you how to pay your membership fees. Membership of STEP offers professionals a number of benefits including opportunities to network, learn and share insights and knowldge across borders and practice areas. Members also have the opportunity to get involved in STEP's activities locally, nationally and internationally, from developing their local branch to contributing to technical or public policy debate on a global level. Being a member will keep you up to date, enhance your profile and develop your skills in specific or more extensive areas. To find out more, contact STEP at +44(0)20 3752 3700 or step@step.org. Should you have any queries please do not hesitate to contact the CLTI Team on +44(0)121 362 7733 or cltinternational@centlaw.com.

In order to gain access to this you will need to navigate to www.cltint.com and log in using your unique username and password. You should ensure that you log-on to the platform as soon as possible to access the resources available. Please check the notice board regularly as it will be used to share important course information. We would very much welcome your contribution to this so that all delegates can benefit from an interactive learning experience. Please note that if you are self-funding your access to the platform will not be activated until payment has been received. Please make a note of your candidate number as you will need it for the examination. Please ensure that you take photographic identification with you to the examination. The invigilator will check this before the examination commences. Your Data We are committed to protecting the privacy and security of your personal information. You can find out how we collect, use, share and protect your personal data by visiting our Privacy Policy which can be found online. Your STEP Membership It is mandatory to become a member of STEP and maintain your STEP membership while studying a STEP qualification. If you are new to membership, STEP will contact you within 6-8 weeks of your enrolment to welcome you to the association, provide you with your login details for the STEP website, direct you to information about the Society's Code of Professional Conduct, and tell you how to pay your membership fees. Membership of STEP offers professionals a number of benefits including opportunities to network, learn and share insights and knowledge across borders and practice areas. Members also have the opportunity to get involved in STEP's activities locally, nationally and internationally, from developing their local branch to contributing to technical or public policy debate on a global level. Being a member will keep you up to date, enhance your profile and develop your skills in specific or more extensive areas. To find out more, please see the full list of benefits at http://www.step.org/benfits or contact STEP at   +44(0)20 3752 3700 or step@step.org . ? Should you have any queries please do not hesitate to contact the CLTI team on +44 (0)121 362 7733  or at cltinternational@centlaw.com

Please remember that the course is not available on an assessment only basis. Candidates are required to undertake both the training and assessment elements. Candidates are required to attend a minimum of 70% of the scheduled workshops. Failing to meet this minimum attendance requirement will mean that you are ineligible to undertake the assessments, you will not be eligible for IBF accreditation and you will NOT be eligible to apply for funding. To become eligible, you would be required to make up the missed workshops on the next intake.

NAME: 1029-APAIP Cross Examination
EMAIL_FOOTER__C:
Laptop
For the ‘Open Source Internet investigations course’ and ‘The Effective and Lawful Use of the Internet in Investigations’ each delegate attending this course is required to bring with them to the training a lap top (not a tablet) which enables the use of WIFI.  The lap top must be free from network administrator lockdown.
 
Submission of Statement/Report 
For the ‘Part 1 - Advanced Statement Report Writing - Written Evidence and Part 2 - Giving Evidence - Witness Familiarisation’ course, you are required to submit a statement or report, written by either yourself or a colleague, to Bond Solon four weeks in advance of the training. Please ensure that this is not from an on-going case that you or your organisation may be involved in. If you are unable to provide a statement or a report, one will be provided for you on the day.
 
Assessment Marking and Edexcel Registration Fees
You have opted to undertake the assessments linked to the course(s) that you have booked. Please find below a breakdown of the additional fees for the:
 
Marking of Assessments
 
£25.00 + VAT per 2 day course
 
Registration Fees
 
For a Certificate the payment is currently £90.00 + VAT per person for the registration of the 8-day Advanced Professional Certificate in Investigative Practice which includes the Edexcel verification and award. 
 
For an Award the payment is currently £45.00 + VAT per person for the registration of each Award (2-day module only) which includes the Edexcel verification and award.
 
For an Award the payment is currently £55.00 + VAT per person for the registration of the 3-day Professional Award in Complaints Handling and Investigation which includes the Edexcel verification and award.
 
Please note that all Registration fees are non-refundable.
               
Assessment Process
Please find attached
  • Assessment Manual
  • QA Registration Form
 
Please read both documents which will provide you with further details on the assessment process and what you will be required to do. Please print a copy of the assessment manual, and take it with you to all training modules
 
Please note the QFORM100 must be submitted to the following email address Info@bondsolon.com  // joannewaddoups@qa-associates.co.uk (Delete as appropriate)
 
Invoicing
Your invoice for the course and marking of assessments will be sent in the next few days.
Please note that on receipt of your registration form, our Independent Assessment Centre, QA Associates will invoice you for Registration fees [Delete if not applicable].
 
All bookings are subject to our Terms and Conditions attached. 
 
If you have any queries in relation to this email and the supporting attachments, please contact me. 
 
We hope you enjoy the course.

Please note that it is compulsory to complete the assessment on the Core Unit BEFORE attending the workshop. The assessment consists of 60 multi choice questions. It is essential that you both read and understand the entire Core Unit course material before taking the assessment and we recommend you set aside 12-16 hours study.

The questions are not designed to assess your general experience but to test your knowledge of the course materials and your ability to apply that learning in an examination environment.  During the workshop you will have an opportunity to examine and consider practical examples and situations relevant to your learning.

AFTER you have attended the workshop you will then be able to select your four elective units to study and complete before the final assessment deadline listed above.

Please note your firm will be charged if you withdraw before the end of the course or if you fail to complete the course and attend the workshop on the planned date.

Please note that it is compulsory to complete the assessment on the Core Unit and the self-led learning BEFORE attending the live online learning sessions. The assessment consists of 60 multi choice questions. It is essential that you both read and understand the entire Core Unit course material before taking the assessment and we recommend you set aside 12-16 hours study.

The questions are not designed to assess your general experience but to test your knowledge of the course materials and your ability to apply that learning in an examination environment.  During the live learning  you will have an opportunity to examine and consider practical examples and situations relevant to your learning.

AFTER you’ve completed the self-led online learning and attended the live online sessions, you will be able to select your four elective units to study and complete before the final assessment deadline listed above.

Please note your firm will be charged if you withdraw before the end of the course or if you fail to complete the course and attend the workshop on the planned date.

We hope you enjoy the course and if you need to get in touch with us or your tutor at any point, please do so by emailing us at clientservices@int-comp.org or calling us on +44 (0)121 362 7708.
EMAIL_HEADER__C:
To access the course materials please click here https://wilmingtonlearninghub.com/login/index.php?theme=HSBC%20%28ICA%29 and use the login details above.

We advise students to access the materials using either Chrome or Firefox as there are some technical issues when using Internet Explorer.

The course uses an integrated learning methodology consisting of:
•        an online learning platform
•        study and support material
•        online multiple-choice assessment 
•        self-led online learning 
•        attendance of 2 live online learning sessions 
•        4 elective units - to be completed by the final assessment date listed below.

The date and time of your live learning sessions are listed below:

Please remember that the course is not available on an assessment only basis. Candidates are required to undertake both the training and assessment elements. Candidates are required to attend a minimum of 70% of the scheduled workshops. Failing to meet this minimum attendance requirement will mean that you are ineligible to undertake the assessments, you will not be eligible for IBF accreditation and you will NOT be eligible to apply for funding. To become eligible, you would be required to make up the missed classes on the next intake.

Если у вас возникнут какие-либо вопросы, свяжитесь с нами по электронной почте studentservices@int-comp.org или позвонив нам по телефону +44 (0) 121 362 7534. Мы надеемся, что вам понравится ваше обучение.
EMAIL_HEADER__C:
Чтобы получить доступ к материалам курса, перейдите на вебсайт ICA и нажмите на синюю вкладку "Вход в курс".  При первом входе в систему вам будет предложено изменить пароль. Если вы проходили обучение у нас раньше или уже являетесь членом ICA, вы можете использовать свои существующие данные для входа.

У вас будет доступ к курсу на три месяца и вы сможете сдать онлайн-экзамен в любой момент в течение этого периода.

Обратите внимание, что вы получите отдельное подтверждение бронирования, касающееся вашего членства, а доступ к вашим членским ресурсам можно получить, нажав на розовую вкладку "Вход для участников". 

Вот основные даты вашего курса, и мы будем отправлять вам напоминание по электронной почте за две недели до каждой даты.

If you are new to membership, STEP will contact you within 6-8 weeks of your enrolment to welcome you to membership, provide you with your login details for the STEP website, direct you to information about the STEP?s Code of Professional Conduct, and tell you how to pay your membership fees. Membership of STEP demonstrates a commitment to high professional standards and continued professional development and offers a number of benefits, including opportunities to network, learn and share insights and knowledge across borders and practice areas. You will also have the opportunity to enhance your profile through our Member Directory and develop your skills in specific or more extensive areas via our CPD resources. To find out more, contact STEP at +44(0)20 3752 3700 or step@step.org. Your Data

We are committed to protecting the privacy and security of your personal information. You can find out how we collect, use, share and protect your personal data by visiting our Privacy Policy which can be found online.

Your STEP Membership

It is mandatory to become a member of STEP and maintain your STEP membership while studying a STEP qualification. If you are new to membership, STEP will contact you within 6-8 weeks of your enrolment to welcome you to membership, provide you with your login details for the STEP website, direct you to information about the STEP’s Code of Professional Conduct, and tell you how to pay your membership fees. Membership of STEP demonstrates a commitment to high professional standards and continued professional development and offers a number of benefits, including opportunities to network, learn and share insights and knowledge across borders and practice areas. You will also have the opportunity to enhance your profile through our Member Directory and develop your skills in specific or more extensive areas via our CPD resources. To find out more, contact STEP at +44(0)20 3752 3700 or step@step.org.

Should you have any queries please do not hesitate to contact the CLTI team on +44 (0)121 362 7733 or at cltinternational@centlaw.com

EMAIL_FOOTER__C:
All training commences promptly at 9.30am and concludes at approximately 5.00pm.
Please note 3-4 weeks prior to the course date a calendar invitation will be sent to you and will include the platform link and the course materials.

Pre-course work
For the 'Responding to Complaints- Letter and Report Writing' course, you are required to submit a statement or report, which has been fully anonymised and which is not for current or impending legal proceedings to Bond Solon four weeks in advance of the training. If you are unable to provide a statement or a report, one will be provided for you on the day of the training.

Assessment Marking and Registration Fees
You have opted to undertake the assessments linked to the course(s) that you have booked. Please find below a breakdown of the additional fees for the:

Marking of Assessments 
£30.00 + VAT per 1 day course 

Registration Fees

For an Award the payment is currently £63.25 + VAT per person for the registration of the 3-day Professional Award in Complaints Handling and Investigation programme, which includes the Pearson (formerly referred to as Edexcel) verification and award. 

Please note that all Registration fees are non-refundable and you will ONLY be registered once your form has been received.

Please note the QFORM100 must be submitted to the following email address joannewaddoups@qa-associates.co.uk and QA Associates (our independent assessment centre) will invoice you for the fee. Please click HERE to download the form. 

If you require an invoice from Bond Solon instead, please click HERE to download the QFORM100X form and submit the form to info@bondsolon.com

Invoice – The invoice will be emailed to you separately (unless payment has already been received). Please click HERE to view the terms and conditions.

Should you have any queries in relation to the courses, please do not hesitate to contact us on 020 7549 2549.

We look forward to seeing you at the training.

Kind regards
Bond Solon Training Ltd
020 7549 2549
www.bondsolon.com

NAME: ICA Diploma in Financial Crime Compliance Module 1 (Specialist) (IH)
EMAIL_FOOTER__C:
Please remember that the course is not available on an assessment only basis. Candidates are required to undertake both the training and assessment elements. Candidates are required to attend a minimum of 70% of the scheduled workshops. Failing to meet this minimum attendance requirement will mean that you are ineligible to undertake the assessments, you will not be eligible for IBF accreditation and you will NOT be eligible to apply for funding. To become eligible, you would be required to make up the missed classes on the next intake.
Attending the workshops really helps to bring the learning to life and also provides guidance on how to approach your assessments. You’ll also get to meet other people on your course and benefit from shared experiences.

Your candidate number is listed at the top of this email and where possible should be quoted in all contact with us. You will also need this when submitting your ICA assessments.

We hope you enjoy the course and if you need to get in touch with us or your tutor at any point, please do so through the Q&A platform on the Learning Platform, by emailing us at  studentadmin@int-comp.com or calling us at +65 6500 0010.

To access your course materials go to the ICA website click on the blue "Course Login" tab.   When you log in for the first time you will be prompted to change your password. If you've studied with us before or are already an ICA member you can use your existing login details.

Please note you will receive a separate booking confirmation regarding your membership and your member resources are available by clicking on the pink "Member Login" tab.

Here are the key dates for your course and we'll send you an email reminder two weeks before each date.

EMAIL_FOOTER__C:
Le recomendamos que asista a todos los talleres ya que realmente ayudan a aplicar lo aprendido a la vida real, y proporcionan orientación sobre la forma de realizar su examen. También podrá conocer a otras personas de su curso y beneficiarse de las experiencias compartidas.
 
Su número de candidato aparece en la parte superior de este correo electrónico y deberá mencionarlo siempre que sea posible cuando se ponga en contacto con nosotros. También tendrá que facilitarlo cuando envíe sus evaluaciones ICA.
 
Si está en LinkedIn, por favor únase a la red de ICT y al Grupo de Estudio aquí https://www.linkedin.com/groups/4246170 y tómese un momento para seguirnos en Twitter y Facebook https://twitter.com/ictcompliance https://www.facebook.com/ictcompliance, para actualizaciones y consejos útiles.
 
Esperamos que disfrute el curso. Si necesita ponerse en contacto con nosotros o con su tutor en cualquier momento, por favor hágalo a través de la Plataforma de Preguntas y Respuestas de la Plataforma de Aprendizaje, por correo electrónico a ict@int-comp.com o llamando al teléfono +44 (0) 121 362 7534.

EMAIL_FOOTER__C: All course materials are provided via our online learning platform. In order to gain access to this you will need to navigate to www.cltint.com and log in using your unique username and password. You should ensure that you log-on to the platform as soon as possible to access the resources available. Please check the notice board regularly as it will be used to share important course information. We would very much welcome your contribution to this so that all delegates can benefit from an interactive learning experience. Please note that if you are self-funding your access to the platform will not be activated until payment has been received . Please make a note of your candidate ID number as you will need it for the examination. Please ensure that you take photographic identification with you to the examination. The invigilator will check this before the examination commences. Your Data We are committed to protecting the privacy and security of your personal information. You can find out how we collect, use, share and protect your personal data by visiting our Privacy Policy which can be found online. Your STEP Membership It is mandatory to become a member of STEP and maintain your STEP membership while studying a STEP qualification. If you are new to membership, STEP will contact you within 6-8 weeks of your enrolment to welcome you to the association, provide you with your login details for the STEP website, direct you to information about the Society's Code of Professional Conduct, and tell you how to pay your membership fees. Membership of STEP offers professionals a number of benefits including opportunities to network, learn and share insights and knowledge across borders and practice areas. Members also have the opportunity to get involved in STEP's activities locally, nationally and internationally, from developing their local branch to contributing to technical or public policy debate on a global level. Being a member will keep you up to date, enhance your profile and develop your skills in specific or more extensive areas. To find out more, contact STEP at +44(0)20 3752 3700 or step@step.org. Should you have any queries please do not hesitate to contact the CLTI Team on +44(0)121 362 7733 or cltinternational@centlaw.com.

EMAIL_HEADER__C:
Para acceder al material de su curso, vaya a la página web de ICA y haga clic en la pestaña de color azul «Inicio de sesión del curso».  Cuando inicie sesión por primera vez, se le pedirá que cambie la contraseña. Si no es la primera vez que estudia con nosotros o si ya es miembro de ICA, puede usar sus datos de inicio de sesión.

Podrá acceder al curso durante tres meses y podrá hacer el examen virtual en cualquier momento dentro de ese plazo.

Tenga en cuenta que va a recibir una confirmación de reserva independiente en relación con su inscripción, y los recursos a los que tiene acceso por ser miembro están disponibles en la pestaña «Inicio de sesión de miembros». 

Estas son las principales fechas de su curso. Le enviaremos un recordatorio por correo electrónico dos semanas antes de cada una de ellas.

EMAIL_FOOTER__C: All course materials are provided via our online learning platform. In order to gain access to this you will need to navigate to www.cltint.com and log in using your unique username and password. You should ensure that you log-on to the platform as soon as possible to access the resources available. Please check the notice board regularly as it will be used to share important course information. We would very much welcome your contribution to this so that all delegates can benefit from an interactive learning experience. Please note that if you are self-funding your access to the platform will not be activated until payment has been received . Please make a note of your candidate ID number as you will need it for the examination. Please ensure that you take photographic identification with you to the examination. The invigilator will check this before the examination commences. Your Data We are committed to protecting the privacy and security of your personal information. You can find out how we collect, use, share and protect your personal data by visiting our Privacy Policy which can be found online. Your STEP Membership It is mandatory to become a member of STEP and maintain your STEP membership while studying a STEP qualification. If you are new to membership, STEP will contact you within 6-8 weeks of your enrolment to welcome you to the association, provide you with your login details for the STEP website, direct you to information about the Society's Code of Professional Conduct, and tell you how to pay your membership fees. Membership of STEP offers professionals a number of benefits including opportunities to network, learn and share insights and knowledge across borders and practice areas. Members also have the opportunity to get involved in STEP's activities locally, nationally and internationally, from developing their local branch to contributing to technical or public policy debate on a global level. Being a member will keep you up to date, enhance your profile and develop your skills in specific or more extensive areas. To find out more, contact STEP at +44(0)20 3752 3700 or step@step.org. Should you have any queries please do not hesitate to contact the CLTI Team on +44(0)121 362 7733 or cltinternational@centlaw.com.

EMAIL_FOOTER__C:
Please remember that the course is not available on an assessment only basis. Candidates are required to undertake both the training and assessment elements. Candidates are required to attend a minimum of 70% of the scheduled workshops. Failing to meet this minimum attendance requirement will mean that you are ineligible to undertake the assessments, you will not be eligible for IBF accreditation and you will NOT be eligible to apply for funding. To become eligible, you would be required to make up the missed classes on the next intake.

EMAIL_FOOTER__C:
All course materials are provided via our online learning platform. In order to gain access to this you will need to navigate to www.cltint.com and log in using your unique username and password.

You should ensure that you log-on to the platform as soon as possible to access the resources available. Please check the course forum regularly as it will be used to share important course information. We would very much welcome your contribution to this so that all delegates can benefit from an interactive learning experience.

Please note that if you are self-funding your access to the platform will not be activated until payment has been received.

Please make a note of your candidate number as you will need it for the examination. Please also ensure that you take photographic identification with you to the examination. The invigilator will check this before the examination commences.

If you are not already a STEP member, STEP will contact you shortly in regard to this. If you do not receive anything within the next 6 - 8 weeks, please contact step@step.org or telephone +44(0)20 3752 3700.

Should you have any queries please do not hesitate to contact the CLTI team on +44 (0)121 362 7733 or at cltinternational@centlaw.com

NAME: ICA Certificate in Ethics Leadership for Senior Managers and Senior FA Reps
EMAIL_FOOTER__C:
After attending the workshop, you will have 2-month access to the online assessment (12 multiple choice questions exam) via the ICTA Learning Platform. We recommend that you attempt the assessment immediately after the workshop and time will be allocated at the end of the workshop in order for you to do this, via your own electronic device e.g. laptop. Please note that you are given two attempts to pass the exam and you are required to answer 70% of the questions correctly in order to obtain a pass. if you fail both attempts there will be a re-sit fee of $26.75 (inclusive of GST) for subsequent attempts.

Your candidate number is listed at the top of this email and where possible should be quoted in all contact with us. 

If you’re on LinkedIn, please join the ICT Network and Study group here https://www.linkedin.com/groups/4246170 and take the time to follow us on Twitter https://twitter.com/ictcompliance and Facebook https://www.facebook.com/ictcompliance for useful updates and tips.

Did you know that we also offer other modes of learning the 12-hour mandatory FA-CPD in addition to face-to-face workshops? This includes e-Learning modules and blended learning.  Please feel free to get in touch with us if you wish to find out more. Or if you need to contact us, please email studentadmin@int-comp.com or calling us at +65 6500 0010.

NAME: ICA Foundation Certificate in Regulatory Compliance - HSBC
EMAIL_FOOTER__C: To help ensure you gain maximum benefit from the course, you will be required to pass an on-line assessment before attending the workshop. The assessment consists of 25 multi choice questions. It is essential that you both read and understand all course material before taking the assessment . The questions are not designed to assess your general experience but to test your knowledge of the course materials and your ability to apply that learning in an examination environment.  During the workshop you will have an opportunity to examine and consider practical examples and situations relevant to your learning.   Please note that it is compulsory to pass the online assessment BEFORE you attend the workshop. Not everyone has passed the multi-choice assessment first time and therefore you are strongly advised to set aside at least 12-16 hours study before attempting the formal assessment. Your firm will be charged if you withdraw before the end of the course or if you fail to complete the course and attend the workshop on the planned date. We hope you enjoy the course and if you need to get in touch with us or your tutor at any point, please do so by emailing us at clientservices@int-comp.org or calling us on +44 (0)121 362 7518.
EMAIL_HEADER__C: This programme has been designed by the International Compliance Association (ICA) in conjunction with HSBC and leads to an ICA Foundation Certificate in Regulatory Compliance. This is an industry recognised qualification, awarded in conjunction with Alliance Manchester Business School.   The course uses an integrated learning methodology consisting of our online learning platform, study and support material, an online multiple-choice assessment and a one-day interactive workshop.  Your workshop date is below and we'll email you approximately two weeks before the workshop to confirm locations and timings.

Membership of STEP offers professionals a number of benefits including opportunities to network, learn and share insights and knowledge across borders and practice areas. Members also have the opportunity to enhance your profile and develop your skills in specific or more extensive areas. To find out more, contact STEP at   +44(0)20 3752 3700 or step@step.org . ? EMAIL_HEADER__C:
You are required to complete the ICA Specialist Certificate in Money Laundering Risk in Correspondent Banking SCB as part of Standard Chartered Bank’s Correspondent Banking Risk Certification you recently registered for.

The Correspondent Banking Risk Certification consists of internal knowledge/process modules and an external course, run by ICA. The entire certification including the ICA course must be completed within 60 days of registration.

ICA Course Overview:
•    The course consists of reading materials and webinars. A mandatory final assessment must be successfully passed in order to complete the course.
•    Staff have two attempts to pass the final assessment. If unsuccessful, the course is locked and an approval process is initiated which may lead to further delays and result in Overdue status. 

Please be aware of the 60 days timeframe and complete the required learning in the time provided.

NAME: ICA Certificado Avanzado en Cumplimiento Normativo
EMAIL_FOOTER__C:
Le recomendamos que asista a todos los talleres ya que realmente ayudan a aplicar lo aprendido a la vida real, y proporcionan orientación sobre la forma de realizar su examen. También podrá conocer a otras personas de su curso y beneficiarse de las experiencias compartidas.
 
Su número de candidato aparece en la parte superior de este correo electrónico y deberá mencionarlo siempre que sea posible cuando se ponga en contacto con nosotros. También tendrá que facilitarlo cuando envíe sus evaluaciones ICA.
 
Si está en LinkedIn, por favor únase a la red de ICT y al Grupo de Estudio aquí https://www.linkedin.com/groups/4246170 y tómese un momento para seguirnos en Twitter y Facebook https://twitter.com/ictcompliance https://www.facebook.com/ictcompliance, para actualizaciones y consejos útiles.
 
Esperamos que disfrute el curso. Si necesita ponerse en contacto con nosotros o con su tutor en cualquier momento, por favor hágalo a través de la Plataforma de Preguntas y Respuestas de la Plataforma de Aprendizaje, por correo electrónico a ict@int-comp.com o llamando al teléfono +44 (0) 121 362 7534.
EMAIL_HEADER__C: Más abajo podrá ver una lista de las fechas relevantes para su curso. Le enviaremos un correo electrónico aproximadamente dos semanas antes de cada fecha para recordársela y para comunicarle los lugares de celebración y los horarios de los talleres y del examen.

NAME: Advanced Certificate in Fund Administration - Jersey
EMAIL_FOOTER__C:
All course materials are provided via our online learning platform. In order to gain access to this you will need to navigate to www.cltint.com and log in using your unique username and password.

Workshop notes and stationery will be provided on each workshop day. 

Please note that if you are self-funding your access to the platform will not be activated until payment has been received. You should ensure that you log-on to the platform as soon as possible to access the resources available. You are automatically set up to receive (by email) notifications of posts added to the course forum. We would very much welcome your contribution to this so that all delegates can benefit from an interactive learning experience.

Your candidate number should be included in the right hand side of the header on each page of your assignment (for further guidance on the assignment and its submission see the assignment section of the online learning platform). Please make a note of your candidate number as you will need it for the examination. Please also ensure that you take photographic identification with you to the examination. The invigilator will check this before the examination commences.

Your STEP Membership It is mandatory to become a member of STEP and maintain your STEP membership while studying a STEP qualification. If you are new to membership, STEP will contact you within 6-8 weeks of your enrolment to welcome you to the association, provide you with your login details for the STEP website, direct you to information about the Society's Code of Professional Conduct, and tell you how to pay your membership fees. Membership of STEP offers professionals a number of benefits including opportunities to network, learn and share insights and knowledge across borders and practice areas. Members also have the opportunity to enhance your profile and develop your skills in specific or more extensive areas. To find out more, contact STEP at   +44(0)20 3752 3700 or step@step.org . ? EMAIL_FOOTER__C: All of the course materials for the DC Law, Chorus Law and Simplify in-house STEP Certificate in Trust and Estates training programme are provided via our online learning platform. In order to gain access to this you will need to navigate to  www.cltint.com  and log in using your unique username and password above. You should ensure that you log-on to the platform as soon as possible to access the resources available. Please check the course forum regularly as it will be used to share important course information. We would very much welcome your contribution to this so that all delegates can benefit from an interactive learning experience. Please make a note of your candidate number as this is your unique identification number. If you are not already a STEP member, STEP will contact you shortly in regard to this. If you do not receive anything within the next 6 - 8 weeks, please contact  step@step.org  or telephone  +44(0)20 3752 3700. ? Should you have any queries please do not hesitate to contact the CLTI team on +44 (0)121 362 7733  or  cltinternational@centlaw.com

NAME: ICA Certificate in KYC & CDD
EMAIL_FOOTER__C:
Due to the practical nature of this course and the way that it is assessed, attendance at the workshop is mandatory. If you don’t attend a workshop you are likely to be at a disadvantage in your exam so please contact us as an alternative online version will need to be completed to comply with the practical application required.  You’ll also get to meet other people on your course and benefit from shared experiences.  

Once the workshop has taken place you will be able to access the online examination.

Your candidate number is listed at the top of this email and where possible should be quoted in all contact with us.

If you’re on LinkedIn, please join the ICT Network and Study group here https://www.linkedin.com/groups/4246170 and take the time to follow us on Twitter https://twitter.com/ictcompliance and Facebook https://www.facebook.com/ictcompliance for useful updates and tips.

We hope you enjoy the course and if you need to get in touch with us or your tutor at any point, please do so through the Q&A platform on the Learning Platform, by emailing us at ict@int-comp.com or calling us on +44(0)121 362 7534.
EMAIL_HEADER__C:
Please take the time to review all of the material on the learning platform and make use of the support and guidance offered to you – you’ll find it invaluable when preparing for your online examination.
